==English==

===Etymology===
Prefix "neo-" (from greek 'neos'= "new") and "tropical" (from greek 'tropikos', referring to where the length of the day equals that of the night)

===Noun===
'''neotropics'''
# The [[neotropic ecozone]], a [[terrestrial]] [[ecoregion]] which includes [[South America]], [[Central America]], and the [[Caribbean]].

